Creating a joyful and harmonious musical sequence using the letters from the phrases "joyful noise" and "singing out with every breath" involves selecting notes from the musical alphabet (A, B, C, D, E, F, G) that appear in these phrases. Let's extract those letters and create a sequence.

From "joyful noise" and "singing out with every breath", we have the musical notes: A, B, C, D, E, F, G.

Now, let's create a joyful and harmonious sequence using these notes without repeating any notes:

Sequence: C, E, G, A, B, D, F

Here is the LaTeX code to represent this musical sequence:

```latex
\documentclass{standalone}
\usepackage{musicography}

\begin{document}
\begin{music}
  \instrumentnumber{1}
  \setname1{Melody}
  \setstaffs1{1}
  \generalmeter{\meterfrac{4}{4}}
  \generalsignature{-3}
  \startextract
    \notes \ibbu0C2 \qb0C \tbbu0 \qb0E \en \bar
    \notes \ibbu0G2 \qb0G \tbbu0 \qb0A \en \bar
    \notes \ibbu0B2 \qb0B \tbbu0 \qb0D \en \bar
    \notes \ibbu0F2 \qb0F \en \bar
  \zendextract
\end{music}
\end{document}
```

This code will produce a musical score with the sequence C, E, G, A, B, D, F, which should sound joyful and harmonious when played.
